Rating: 1
I have to admit that I don't know what all the fuss is over this recipe.....I followed it pretty much exactly and although the presentation was lovely, I found the crab salad to be quite bland and the dressing was downright yucky....maybe I did something wrong? I don't know, but with the leftovers I added one egg, some breadcrumbs and a bit of worcesterchire sauce and made crab cakes out of the rest. Now those were pretty good! I ditched the dressing and served them with tartar sauce. Oh well...

Rating: 1
While I didn't care for the crab salad at all -- the apples and vegetables overwhelm the -- the dressing is excellent. I find that the dressing stores well in the refrigerator and is great on a dinner salad. Tomorrow, I'll make a crab salad of my own to serve on endive with the dressing.

